                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13500147" author="ikelly" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 11:04:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a preliminary patch, though I don&apos;t know if it&apos;s sufficient. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hustlmsp&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hustlmsp&quot;&gt;Sijie Guo&lt;/a&gt; Could you take a look at this when you get a chance?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13504310" author="hustlmsp" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 02:26:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the behavior before &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-70&quot; title=&quot;reduce or multiplex subscription connections to a hub server&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-70&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-70&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is that we should do resubscribe until succeed if resubscribe is enabled. If you stopped resubscribing, the subscriber got nothing notified about its subscription is stopped unless it registered listener about it. So I think we should keep this behavior but log some critical messages after a specific retires.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13508622" author="ikelly" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 10:10:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resubscribe until success isn&apos;t a problem. The problem here is that there&apos;s a tight loop, so this will overflow the stack.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13509461" author="hustlmsp" created="Tue, 4 Dec 2012 02:54:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;added a patch to stop retrying resubscribe if the channel manager is closed. after this patch, it would also resolve the issue described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-489&quot; title=&quot;OOM running hedwig tests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-489&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-489&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13509837" author="ikelly" created="Tue, 4 Dec 2012 16:28:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the change. will test and push it in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13509881" author="ikelly" created="Tue, 4 Dec 2012 17:28:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as r1417046. Thanks Sijie.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
